Preheat your oven to 220°C. Bring a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} to the boil. Peel the @baking potato{1}, chop into 2cm chunks and add to the pan. Boil until you can easily slip a knife through them, ~{12-15%minutes}, then drain in a #colander{} and allow to steam dry.

In the meantime, roughly chop the @coriander{1}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Zest the @lime{1/2} then chop in half. Pop the @hot smoked salmon{150%g} in a #bowl{}. Add the @sweet chilli sauce{32%g}, @plain flour{24%g}, lime zest, @Thai style spice mix{1/2} (careful, it's hot! Don't use it all if you're not a fan of heat!) and half the coriander. Season with @salt and @pepper, then mix together with your hands or a #spoon{} until well combined. Set aside.

Using a #peeler{}, peel the @mango{1/2} then stand upright on your #chopping board{}. Slice down either side of the stone to give you 2 'cheeks'. Slice any remaining flesh from the stone, then thinly slice the mango widthways. Discard the stone. Halve the @baby plum tomatoes{125}(halved). Halve the @red chilli{1/2} lengthways, deseed then finely chop. Squeeze the lime juice into a medium-sized bowl. Add the @olive oil{1%tbsp} a small pinch of chilli and the remaining coriander. Season with @salt and @pepper and mix together. Pop the mango and tomatoes into the bowl, mix again and set aside.

> You can keep the chilli seeds if you want extra heat!

Next, pop the @panko breadcrumbs{25%g} on a #plate{}, drizzle over the @olive oil{1%tbsp} and mix to coat the crumbs thoroughly. Once you've drained the potatoes, leave them to cool for a few minutes then add into the bowl with the salmon. Use a #fork{} or #potato masher{} to mash everything together, then use your hands to form the mixture into 2 fishcakes per person. Lay the cakes in the breadcrumbs and turn carefully to coat each side. Gently press the breadcrumbs into the cake so that they stick.

Put the fishcakes onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{} and drizzle a little oil on top. Bake on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, halve the @sugar snap peas{80%g} lengthways. Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @salted peanuts{25%g}(roughly chopped) into small pieces. Add the peanuts to the mango and tomato bowl.

When the fishcakes have 5 mins cooking time left, heat a drizzle of oil in a #frying pan{} on medium high heat. Once hot, add the sugar snaps and @king prawns{120%g} and stir fry until the prawns are cooked, ~{3-4%minutes}. Add the garlic and cook for ~{1%minute} more.

> IMPORTANT: The prawns are cooked when pink on the outside and opaque in the middle.

Spoon the sugar snaps and prawns into the bowl with the salsa and toss everything together. Once the fishcakes are cooked pop them on your plates and serve with the prawn and mango salsa. Enjoy.